<section class="container py-4">
  <h2>Web Applications</h2>
  <p>Interactive tools for text analysis and language learning are shown below. More tools will be added over the coming months.</p>

  <div class="row g-4 mt-2">
    <div class="col-md-6 col-lg-4">
      <div class="card h-100">
        <div class="card-body">
          <h5 class="card-title"><i class="bi bi-clock-history me-2 text-dark"></i><span style="background:#ff8c00;color:#fff;font-size:0.65em;font-weight:700;padding:0.15em 0.55em;border-radius:0.4em;margin-right:0.45em;vertical-align:middle;">New</span>Tense Identifier</h5>
          <p class="card-text">Identifies the tense and voice of finite verb phrases. Tensed verbs are named according to the 12 pedagogic tenses while modalized verb phrases are classified by type of modal and the subsequent structure.</p>
          <a href="https://jb11.org/new_tense_identifier/" class="btn btn-outline-primary btn-sm" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Open Tool</a>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
    <div class="col-md-6 col-lg-4">
      <div class="card h-100">
        <div class="card-body">
          <h5 class="card-title"><i class="bi bi-mic me-2 text-dark"></i><span style="background:#ff8c00;color:#fff;font-size:0.65em;font-weight:700;padding:0.15em 0.55em;border-radius:0.4em;margin-right:0.45em;vertical-align:middle;">New</span>Pronunciation Scaffolder</h5>
          <p class="card-text">Practise reading English aloud by following the visualizations to help with intonation, stress and sounds. This improved version incorporates an autoscrolling feature and multiple voices.</p>
          <a href="https://jb11.org/pronscaff/" class="btn btn-outline-primary btn-sm" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Open Tool</a>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
    <div class="col-md-6 col-lg-4">
      <div class="card h-100">
        <div class="card-body">
          <h5 class="card-title"><i class="bi bi-star me-2 text-dark"></i>Spelling Stars</h5>
          <p class="card-text">Spell words that you hear. A mastery learning app that harnessed adaptive testing for young learners through to adults. Words are categorized by both frequency and difficulty.</p>
          <a href="https://jb11.org/spelling_app/" class="btn btn-outline-primary btn-sm" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Open Tool</a>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
    <div class="col-md-6 col-lg-4">
      <div class="card h-100">
        <div class="card-body">
          <h5 class="card-title"><i class="bi bi-eye me-2 text-dark"></i>Feature visualizer</h5>
          <p class="card-text">Raise your awareness of the genre of short computer science research articles. This was designed primarily for learners whose first language is not English.</p>
          <a href="https://fv.rt247a.ddns.me/" class="btn btn-outline-primary btn-sm" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Open Tool</a>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
    <div class="col-md-6 col-lg-4">
      <div class="card h-100">
        <div class="card-body">
          <h5 class="card-title"><i class="bi bi-layers me-2 text-dark"></i><span style="background:#ff8c00;color:#fff;font-size:0.65em;font-weight:700;padding:0.15em 0.55em;border-radius:0.4em;margin-right:0.45em;vertical-align:middle;">New</span>Move Visualizer</h5>
          <p class="card-text">Explore how rhetorical move structure (Introduction, Purpose, Method, Result, Discussion) in scientific research abstracts varies within and across different subject domains. Includes 1,000 annotated abstracts across 10 disciplines.</p>
          <a href="https://john6938.github.io/move-visualizer/" class="btn btn-outline-primary btn-sm" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Open Tool</a>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
    <div class="col-md-6 col-lg-4">
      <div class="card h-100">
        <div class="card-body">
          <h5 class="card-title"><i class="bi bi-spell-check me-2 text-dark"></i><span style="background:#ff8c00;color:#fff;font-size:0.65em;font-weight:700;padding:0.15em 0.55em;border-radius:0.4em;margin-right:0.45em;vertical-align:middle;">New</span>CompSci Error Detector</h5>
          <p class="card-text">Check scientific writing for accuracy, brevity, clarity, objectivity and formality. Designed for computer science researchers and students writing in English as an additional language.</p>
          <a href="https://john6938.github.io/error-detector-compsci/" class="btn btn-outline-primary btn-sm" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Open Tool</a>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
    <div class="col-md-6 col-lg-4">
      <div class="card h-100">
        <div class="card-body">
          <h5 class="card-title"><i class="bi bi-diagram-3 me-2 text-dark"></i><span style="background:#ff8c00;color:#fff;font-size:0.65em;font-weight:700;padding:0.15em 0.55em;border-radius:0.4em;margin-right:0.45em;vertical-align:middle;">New</span>Information Structure Analyser</h5>
          <p class="card-text">Identifies and visualizes the linguistic information structure within texts, including the principles of end-weight, information focus, information flow and thematic development.</p>
          <a href="https://john6938.github.io/new_information_structure_detector/" class="btn btn-outline-primary btn-sm" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Open Tool</a>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
    <div class="col-md-6 col-lg-4">
      <div class="card h-100">
        <div class="card-body">
          <h5 class="card-title"><i class="bi bi-tools me-2 text-dark"></i>Teacher Utilities</h5>
          <p class="card-text">A suite of classroom management tools, including: a countdown timer, a student randomizer, an attention getter, a forgive-or-fine wheel, and a reward generator. All run in the browser with no login required.</p>
          <a href="{{ '/tools/teacher-utilities/' | url }}" class="btn btn-outline-primary btn-sm">Open suite</a>
        </div>
      </div>
